  "english": [
    "Rabbi Akiva’s testimony is not needed to teach the basic <i>halakha</i> that a vessel combines its ingredients, which is Torah law; <b>it is necessary only for the remainders of the meal-offering,</b> the part of a meal-offering left over after a fistful of it and its frankincense have been sacrificed on the altar, which is eaten by a priest. In such a case the <i>halakha</i> of combining applies only by rabbinic law, for <b>by Torah law</b> only when an item <b>requires a vessel</b> in order for it to be sanctified does <b>the vessel combine it</b> with regard to impurity, even if its parts are not touching each other. But in the case of something <b>that does not require a vessel,</b> the <b>vessel does not combine it.</b> The remainder of a meal-offering no longer requires a vessel, since it is given to a priest after the fistful is sacrificed, so the flour in a vessel would not be considered combined according to Torah law.",
    "<b>And the Sages came and decreed that even if</b> something <b>does not require a vessel,</b> such as the leftover flour of the meal-offering, the <b>vessel</b> nevertheless <b>combines it.</b>",
    "The Gemara raises a difficulty: It <b>works out well</b> in the case of <b>flour,</b> which can be said to refer to the flour left over from meal-offerings, but with regard to <b>incense and frankincense, what is there to say?</b> In these cases a vessel is certainly required, but if the <i>halakha</i> of combining applies to them from the Torah, why did Rabbi Akiva include them in his list? <b>Rav Naḥman said</b> that <b>Rabba bar Avuh said: For example, if he piled them up on a leather board [<i>kartavla</i>],</b> rather than in a containing vessel. <b>By Torah law</b> a vessel that <b>has an inside combines</b> its ingredients, but <b>one that</b> is flat and <b>does not have an inside does not combine. And the Sages came and decreed that even if it does not have an inside it</b> nevertheless <b>combines</b> what is placed on it.",
    "The Gemara comments: <b>And</b> this opinion <b>of Rabbi Ḥanin’s,</b> that impurity by combining is derived from the Torah, <b>disagrees with</b> the opinion <b>of Rabbi Ḥiyya bar Abba. For Rabbi Ḥiyya bar Abba said</b> that <b>Rabbi Yoḥanan said</b> in reference to our mishna: <b>This mishna was taught based on Rabbi Akiva’s testimony.</b> In other words, the mishna’s teaching that a vessel combines its contents follows the statement of Rabbi Akiva, indicating that it is by rabbinic law, unlike Rabbi Ḥanin, who said that it is based on a source from the Torah.",
    "§ It was taught in the mishna: <b>The fourth degree</b> of impurity, <b>with regard to sacrificial</b> food, is <b>disqualified. It is taught</b> in a <i>baraita</i>: <b>Rabbi Yosei said: From where</b> is it derived with regard <b>to the fourth degree</b> of ritual impurity, that <b>with regard to sacrificial</b> food it <b>is disqualified? It is a logical derivation,</b> by <i>a fortiori</i>: <b>If one who is lacking atonement,</b> an impure person who is obligated to bring an offering to complete his purification process, <b>who is permitted to</b> eat <b><i>teruma</i>,</b> is nevertheless <b>disqualified with regard to</b> the consumption of <b>sacrificial</b> food, as specified in the Torah, then concerning something that is impure to the <b>third</b> degree of ritual impurity, <b>which is disqualified</b> if it is <b><i>teruma</i>, is it not right that it should engender a fourth</b> degree of ritual impurity when it touches <b>sacrificial</b> food? Therefore, <b>we have learned</b> that there is a <b>third</b> degree of impurity with regard <b>to sacrificial food from the Torah, and</b> that there is a <b>fourth</b> degree of impurity <b>from <i>a fortiori</i></b> reasoning.",
    "The above <i>baraita</i> taught that there is a <b>third</b> degree of impurity <b>for sacrificial</b> food <b>from the Torah.</b> The Gemara asks: <b>From where</b> is this derived? <b>As it is written: “And the meat that touches any impure thing shall not be eaten”</b> (Leviticus 7:19). <b>Is it not</b> so that <b>we are not dealing</b> in that verse with meat that touches any “impure thing” at all, even <b>if it touched</b> something that is of the <b>second</b> degree of ritual impurity, which is also called an “impure thing”? <b>And</b> yet <b>the Merciful One states</b> with regard to that meat, which having touched a second-degree impurity is now impure to the third degree: <b>“It shall not be eaten,”</b> meaning that it has been rendered unfit due to impurity. And as for the <i>baraita’s</i> statement that the <b>fourth</b> level of impurity is derived <b>by an <i>a fortiori</i> inference –</b> it is <b>as we said</b> just above, the <i>a fortiori</i> inference put forth by Rabbi Yosei.",
    "§ It was taught in the mishna: <b>And with regard to <i>teruma</i>, if</b> one of one’s hands <b>became impure</b> with impurity by rabbinic law that renders only the hands impure, its counterpart, the other hand, remains pure. But with regard to sacrificial food, if one hand becomes impure he must immerse them both. <b>Rav Sheizevi said:</b> When they said that with regard to sacrificial food a hand that is rendered impure renders the other hand impure as well, <b>they taught</b> this only for a situation <b>when</b> the pure hand is <b>in contact</b> with the sacrificial food when the impure hand touches it. <b>But</b> if the pure hand is <b>not in contact</b> with the sacrificial food, <b>no,</b> the pure hand is not rendered impure by touching the impure hand. According to Rav Sheizevi, the Sages enacted the decree that one hand renders the other impure because they were concerned that the impure hand may have touched the sacrificial food directly without being noticed. Therefore, the decree applies only when the pure hand is touching the sacrificial food.",
    "<b>Abaye raised an objection to</b> Rav Sheizevi from the following teaching: Even <b>a dry hand</b> that is impure <b>renders its counterpart,</b> i.e., the other hand, <b>impure, to</b> the extent that the second hand will now <b>render impure</b> any food that it touches. This is true with regard <b>to sacrificial</b> food <b>but not</b> with regard <b>to <i>teruma</i>.</b> This is <b>the statement of Rabbi</b> Yehuda HaNasi. <b>Rabbi Yosei, son of Rabbi Yehuda, says:</b> The second hand is not rendered impure to such a severe extent. It can merely <b>disqualify</b> sacrificial food that it touches, by rendering it impure to the fourth degree, <b>but not render</b> it <b>impure</b> with third-degree impurity.",
    "<b>Granted, if you say</b> that the second hand becomes impure even <b>when it is not in contact</b> with the sacrificial food, <b>this</b> would explain <b>the noteworthiness of a dry</b> hand rendering its counterpart impure. It teaches that even though normally a dry hand would not render another hand impure, the Sages nevertheless declared it impure with regard to sacrificial food. <b>But if you say</b> that when the second hand is <b>in contact</b> with sacrificial food, <b>yes,</b> the decree that the second hand becomes impure applies, lest the impure hand touch the sacrificial food directly, but <b>when it is not in contact, no,</b> the decree does not apply, then <b>what is the noteworthiness</b> of stating that it applies in the case of a <b>dry</b> hand?",
    "<b>It was also stated</b> that <i>amora’im</i> disputed a similar issue: <b>Reish Lakish said: They taught</b> that one hand renders the other impure <b>only</b> if the second hand is <b>his</b> own <b>hand,</b>"
  ],
  "gemara": [
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "<span class=\"sentence\" id=\"0\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>לֹא נִצְרְכָא אֶלָּא לִשְׁיָרֵי מִנְחָה. דְּאוֹרָיְיתָא,",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "צָרִיךְ לִכְלִי — הַכְּלִי מְצָרְפוֹ, שֶׁאֵין צָרִיךְ לִכְלִי — אֵין",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "כְּלִי מְצָרְפוֹ. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"1\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>וַאֲתוֹ רַבָּנַן וּגְזַרוּ דְּאַף עַל גַּב דְּאֵינוֹ",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "צָרִיךְ לִכְלִי — כְּלִי מְצָרְפוֹ. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"2\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>תִּינַח סֹלֶת, קְטוֹרֶת",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וּלְבוֹנָה מַאי אִיכָּא לְמֵימַר? אָמַר <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rav Naḥman bar Ya’akov, third-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"2285\" data-full-name=\"Rav Naḥman bar Ya’akov\" data-name-he=\"רב נחמן בר יעקב\">רַב נַחְמָן</span>",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אָמַר <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rav Adda bar Abba, second-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"2586\" data-full-name=\"Rav Adda bar Abba\" data-name-he=\"רבה בר אבוה\">רַבָּה בַּר אֲבוּהּ</span>: כְּגוֹן שֶׁצְּבָרָן עַל גַּבֵּי",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "קַרְטְבֻלָא. דְּאוֹרָיְיתָא, יֵשׁ לוֹ תּוֹךְ — מְצָרֵף, אֵין",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "לוֹ תּוֹךְ — אֵינוֹ מְצָרֵף, וַאֲתוֹ רַבָּנַן וְתַקִּינוּ דְּאַף עַל גַּב",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "דְּאֵין לוֹ תּוֹךְ — מְצָרֵף. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"3\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>וּפְלִיגָא <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rav Ḥanin I, second-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"1305\" data-full-name=\"Rav Ḥanin I\" data-name-he=\"רב חנין\">דְּרַבִּי חָנִין</span> אַדְּ<span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Yehuda HaNasi, sixth-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"1508\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Yehuda HaNasi\" data-name-he=\"רבי יהודה הנשיא\">רַבִּי</span>",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "חִיָּיא בַּר אַבָּא. דְּאָמַר <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rabbi Ḥiyya bar Abba, third-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"1091\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Ḥiyya bar Abba\" data-name-he=\"רבי חייא בר אבא\">רַבִּי חִיָּיא בַּר אַבָּא</span> אָמַר <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rabbi Yoḥanan II, second-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"1570\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Yoḥanan II\" data-name-he=\"רבי יוחנן\" data-crossline-group=\"name-ref-crossline-23375\">רַבִּי</span>",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "<span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rabbi Yoḥanan II, second-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"1570\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Yoḥanan II\" data-name-he=\"רבי יוחנן\" data-crossline-group=\"name-ref-crossline-23375\">יוֹחָנָן</span>: מֵעֵדוּתוֹ שֶׁל <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Akiva I, fourth-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"2465\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Akiva I\" data-name-he=\"רבי עקיבא בן יוסף\">רַבִּי עֲקִיבָא</span> נִשְׁנֵית מִשְׁנָה זוֹ. ",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "<span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-vilna-piska\" data-sugya-kind=\"vilna-piska\" data-sugya-id=\"89\" data-raw-symbol=\"׃\">׃</span> <span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-steinsaltz\" data-sugya-kind=\"steinsaltz\" data-sugya-id=\"104\" data-sentence-id=\"4\" data-steinsaltz-label=\"א\">§</span> <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"4\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>הָרְבִיעִי בַּקֹּדֶשׁ פָּסוּל<span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-vilna-piska\" data-sugya-kind=\"vilna-piska\" data-sugya-id=\"90\" data-raw-symbol=\"׃\">׃</span> תַּנְיָא, אָמַר <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Yosei, fifth-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"1657\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Yosei\" data-name-he=\"רבי יוסי בן חלפתא\">רַבִּי יוֹסֵי</span>:",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מִנַּיִן לָרְבִיעִי בַּקֹּדֶשׁ שֶׁהוּא פָּסוּל — וְדִין הוּא:",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וּמָה מְחוּסַּר כִּפּוּרִים שֶׁמּוּתָּר בַּתְּרוּמָה — פָּסוּל",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "בַּקֹּדֶשׁ, שְׁלִישִׁי שֶׁפָּסוּל בַּתְּרוּמָה — אֵינוֹ דִּין",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "שֶׁיַּעֲשֶׂה רְבִיעִי לַקֹּדֶשׁ? וְלָמַדְנוּ שְׁלִישִׁי לַקֹּדֶשׁ",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מִן הַתּוֹרָה, וּרְבִיעִי בְּקַל וָחוֹמֶר. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"5\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>שְׁלִישִׁי לַקֹּדֶשׁ מִן",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "הַתּוֹרָה מִנַּיִן? דִּכְתִיב: ״וְהַבָּשָׂר אֲשֶׁר יִגַּע",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "בְּכׇל טָמֵא לֹא יֵאָכֵל״, מִי לָא עָסְקִינַן דִּנְגַע",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "בְּשֵׁנִי, וְקָאָמַר רַחֲמָנָא ״לֹא יֵאָכֵל״. רְבִיעִי מִקַּל וָחוֹמֶר —",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "הָא דַּאֲמַרַן<span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-vilna-piska\" data-sugya-kind=\"vilna-piska\" data-sugya-id=\"91\" data-raw-symbol=\"׃\">׃</span> <span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-steinsaltz\" data-sugya-kind=\"steinsaltz\" data-sugya-id=\"105\" data-sentence-id=\"6\" data-steinsaltz-label=\"ב\">§</span> <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"6\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>וּבַתְּרוּמָה אִם נִטְמֵאת",
      "segment_ids": [
        6
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "כּוּ׳<span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-vilna-piska\" data-sugya-kind=\"vilna-piska\" data-sugya-id=\"92\" data-raw-symbol=\"׃\">׃</span> אָמַר <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rav Sheizevi, fourth-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"2716\" data-full-name=\"Rav Sheizevi\" data-name-he=\"רב שיזבי\">רַב שֵׁיזְבִי</span>: בְּחִיבּוּרִין שָׁנוּ, אֲבָל",
      "segment_ids": [
        6
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "שֶׁלֹּא בְּחִיבּוּרִין — לֹא. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"7\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>אֵיתִיבֵיהּ <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Abaye, fourth-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"121\" data-full-name=\"Abaye\" data-name-he=\"אביי\">אַבָּיֵי</span>: יָד",
      "segment_ids": [
        7
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "נְגוּבָה מְטַמָּא חֲבֶירְתָּהּ לְטַמֵּא לַקֹּדֶשׁ, אֲבָל",
      "segment_ids": [
        7
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "לֹא לַתְּרוּמָה, דִּבְרֵי רַבִּי. <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Yosei bar Rabbi Yehuda, sixth-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"1695\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Yosei bar Rabbi Yehuda\" data-name-he=\"רבי יוסי ברבי יהודה\">רַבִּי יוֹסֵי בְּרַבִּי יְהוּדָה</span>",
      "segment_ids": [
        7
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אוֹמֵר: לִפְסוֹל, אֲבָל לֹא לְטַמֵּא. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"8\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>אִי אָמְרַתְּ",
      "segment_ids": [
        8
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "בִּשְׁלָמָא שֶׁלֹּא בְּחִיבּוּרִין — הַיְינוּ רְבוּתַיהּ",
      "segment_ids": [
        8
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "דִּנְגוּבָה. אֶלָּא אִי אָמְרַתְּ בְּחִיבּוּרִין — אִין, שֶׁלֹּא בְּחִיבּוּרִין —",
      "segment_ids": [
        8
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "לָא, מַאי רְבוּתָה דִּנְגוּבָה? <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"9\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>אִיתְּמַר",
      "segment_ids": [
        9
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "נָמֵי, אָמַר <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rabbi Shimon ben Lakish, second-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"2879\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Shimon ben Lakish\" data-name-he=\"רבי שמעון בן לקיש\">רֵישׁ לָקִישׁ</span>: לֹא שָׁנוּ אֶלָּא יָדוֹ,",
      "segment_ids": [
        9
      ]
    }
  ],
  "rashi": [
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>לֹא נִצְרְכָא</b> להאי עדות דר' עקיבא דמדרבנן אלא לסולת של שירי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "מנחה: <b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">דאלו</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">מדאורייתא</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">הצריך</span> לִכְלִי.</b> דומיא דקטורת שבכף",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:1:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "דאיירי בה קרא כלי מצרפו ושאינו צריך לכלי כגון שירי מנחה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:1:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "שהן אכילת כהן אין הכלי מצרפן: <b>מַאי אִיכָּא לְמֵימַר</b> הרי צריכין",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:3:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "לכלי: <b>קַרְטְבֻלָא</b> עור שלוק: <b>ופליגא</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:3:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">הא</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">דר&#x27;</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">חנין</span>.</b> דאמר לעיל צירוף",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:3:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "דאורייתא אדר' חייא בר אבא:",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:3:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>מְחוּסַּר כִּפּוּרִים <span class=\"dh-divergent\">כשר</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">לתרומה</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">ופסול</span></b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:5:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>לַקֹּדֶשׁ</b> ביבמות ילפינן לה מקראי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:5:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "בפרק הערל (<a href=\"/yevamot/74b\">יבמות דף עד:</a>): <b>שְׁלִישִׁי</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:5:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>שֶׁפָּסוּל בַּתְּרוּמָה.</b> כדנפקא לן ק\"ו",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:5:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "במסכת סוטה (<a href=\"/sotah/29a\">דף כט.</a>) ומה טבול",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:5:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "יום שמותר במעשר אסור בתרומה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:5:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "שני שפסול במעשר אינו דין שיעשה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:5:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "שלישי בתרומה: <b>אֵינוֹ דִּין שֶׁיַּעֲשֶׂה</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:5:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>רְבִיעִי לַקֹּדֶשׁ.</b> וא\"ת דיו לבא מן",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:5:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "הדין להיות כנדון א\"כ ק\"ו לא צריך",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:5:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "שהרי למדנו שלישי לקדש מן התורה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:5:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "והיכא דמיפריך ק\"ו לא אמרינן דיו",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:5:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "לבא מן הדין להיות כנדון כדאמרינן",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:5:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "בבבא קמא (<a href=\"/bava_kamma/25a\">דף כה.</a>) ולמ\"ד נמי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:5:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "אמרינן דיו הני מעלות דרבנן נינהו",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:5:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "ולאו דאורייתא והאי דנקט ולמדנו",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:5:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "שלישי לקדש מלתא בעלמא היא",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:5:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "דאשמעינן דשלישי לקדש מן התורה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:5:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "הוא: <b>מִי לָא עָסְקִינַן <span class=\"dh-divergent\">כו&#x27;</span></b> מי לא",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:6:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "משתמע (כו') נמי מהאי קרא: <b>דִּנְגַע</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:6:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>בְּשֵׁנִי.</b> דהא אשכחן דאיקרי שני טמא",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:6:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "דכתיב כל אשר בתוכו יטמא וה\"ל",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:6:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "הכלי ראשון ומה שבתוכו שני וקרי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:6:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "ליה טמא וקאמר רחמנא והבשר אשר",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:6:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "יגע בכל טמא בשני וה\"ל שלישי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:6:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "לא יאכל והאי קרא בבשר שלמים",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:6:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "כתיב: <b>בְּחִיבּוּרִין שָׁנוּ.</b> מתניתין",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "דקתני יד מטמאה את חבירתה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "לקדש כגון שבעוד שהיד הטמאה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "נוגעת לטהורה היתה טהורה נוגעת",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "בקדש דגזור רבנן דלמא אתי למינגע",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "טמאה בקדש ולמ\"ד פסול לקמן",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:7:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "לפסול דמעלה בעלמא היא: <b>אֲבָל</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:7:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>שֶׁלֹּא בְּחִיבּוּרִין.</b> שלאחר שפירשה מן הטהורה חזרה טהורה ונגעה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:7:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "בקדש טהור ואין יד מטמאה חבירתה לעשותה אפי' שלישית לפסול:",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:7:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>יָד נְגוּבָה</b> אע\"פ שאין בה משקין: <b>לטמא</b> <b>את</b> <b>הקדש.</b> לעשות",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:8:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        6
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "רביעי: <b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">ר&#x27;</span> יוֹסֵי <span class=\"dh-divergent\">בר&#x27;</span> יְהוּדָה אוֹמֵר</b> חבירתה פוסלת את הקדש",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:8:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        7
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "אבל לא מטמאה: <b>אִי אָמְרַתְּ בִּשְׁלָמָא שֶׁלֹּא בְּחִיבּוּרִין.</b> קאמר דמטמאה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:9:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        7
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "היינו רבותא דנגובה ואע\"ג דנגובה היא כשנגעה בזו ואין לחוש",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:9:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        7
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "שמא נגעה היד הטהורה במשקין שבטמאה שהן ראשונים דכל",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:9:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        7
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "הפוסל את התרומה מטמא משקין להיות תחילה והויא לה הך",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:9:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        7
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "יד נמי שניה מחמת המשקין כמו חבירתה אפילו הכי מטמאה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:9:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        7
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "דמעלה דרבנן היא שהיד מטמאה את חבירתה להעשות שניה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:9:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        7
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "כמותה לקדש אלא אי אמרת לא אמרינן אלא בחיבורין וטעמא",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:9:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        7
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "משום דלמא נגע טמא לקדש מאי רבותא דנגובה אטו יד",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:9:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        7
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "0px",
      "left": "",
      "text": "קמייתא לא מטמיא לה לקדש בלא משקין הלא שניה היא:",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Chagigah 24a:9:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        7
      ]
    }
  ],
